2026-04-28 14:24:34,300 | AGENT | SecurityCompliance Agent answered: To ensure compliance with GDPR and protect sensitive data, we must implement several security measures. Firstly, as stated in our standard data residency policy, all data will be stored within the EU only, ensuring that no personal data is transferred outside the European Union unless an explicit legal basis is established, which aligns with our cross-border transfer policy of prohibiting such transfers by default.

To protect data appropriately, we utilize anonymisation tools such as Microsoft Presidio (self-hosted) and custom NER models. This ensures that any personal data used in our AI-powered information systems is anonymized, reducing the risk of sensitive information being exposed.

We also have experience with GDPR compliance, having appointed a Data Protection Officer (DPO) who can be contacted at dpo@nexus-engineering.it for any data protection inquiries or concerns. Our DPA template is available upon request, facilitating the establishment of data processing agreements that comply with GDPR requirements.

For access control, we enforce multi-factor authentication (MFA) using TOTP and hardware tokens (FIDO2), ensuring that only authorized personnel have access to sensitive data. Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) design experience allows us to manage user permissions effectively, limiting access to data based on the principle of least privilege.

