### Executive Summary

We are pleased to submit a comprehensive proposal for the implementation of an artificial intelligence (AI) solution to assist municipal agents in their daily missions, as requested by the City of Belval. Our consortium, comprising experienced partners with expertise in AI solutions, public sector IT, and smart cities, is well-equipped to deliver a tailored solution that meets the city's requirements. This proposal outlines our understanding of the project's objectives, the proposed solution, compliance with regulatory and technical constraints, budget overview, and conclusion.

### Understanding of Requirements

We have thoroughly reviewed the call for tenders and understand the need for an AI-powered assistance tool that can facilitate access to information, improve the quality of answers, and reduce processing times. The solution must integrate with existing systems, ensure data sovereignty, and comply with regulatory requirements such as GDPR. We also recognize the importance of environmental sustainability and will incorporate measures to reduce energetic consumption.

### Proposed Solution

Our proposed solution leverages our expertise in Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) capabilities and Large Language Models (LLMs). The RAG component will enable the tool to retrieve relevant information from a knowledge base and generate responses that recall applicable rules and suggest actions or verifications. We will employ quantisation methods such as INT8 to reduce energetic consumption and ensure explainability and transparency through source citation, display chain-of-thought, and confidence scoring.

The solution will be deployed on a sovereign cloud infrastructure, ensuring data sovereignty and compliance with regulatory requirements. Our technical architecture will utilize containerization tools, monitoring tools, and API standards to ensure high availability, scalability, and integration with existing systems.

### Compliance & Certifications

We are committed to complying with all relevant regulatory requirements, including GDPR, EU AI Act, and RGPD/GDPR. We have a Data Protection Officer (DPO) appointed and will establish a data processing agreement that complies with GDPR requirements. Our solution will also adhere to the principles of explainability and transparency, ensuring that recommendations or proposals can be understood and justified.

We hold an ISO 27001 certification, which covers the design, development, and operation of AI-powered information systems, demonstrating our commitment to maintaining high standards of information security management. We will also strive for ISO14001 certification by 2026, further emphasizing our dedication to environmental sustainability.

### Budget Overview

Our proposed budget is aligned with the city's allocated budget of 3 million euros over a duration of 4 years. We have estimated a gross margin percentage of 28%, resulting in a projected margin of 840,000 euros. To optimize costs without sacrificing quality, we propose strategies such as rate renegotiation with subcontractors and scope adjustments. Our financial position is stable, with a debt-to-equity ratio and credit line availability that can support negotiations for better terms or investments in cost-saving measures.

### Conclusion

We believe our proposed solution meets the City of Belval's requirements for an AI-powered assistance tool, ensuring data sovereignty, regulatory compliance, and environmental sustainability. Our consortium's expertise in AI solutions, public sector IT, and smart cities makes us a strong partner for this project. We are confident that our solution will improve the efficiency of administrative services and enhance the quality of service rendered to users. We look forward to the opportunity to discuss our proposal in further detail and explore how we can support the city's digital transformation strategy.

Please note that some aspects, such as detailed technical specifications, timelines, and specific resource allocation plans, are not addressed in this proposal due to the lack of explicit information provided by the agents' answers. However, we are committed to providing any additional necessary details during the evaluation process.
